Later Years ==
DiCesare was inactive in the music and entertainment business for many years after selling his share of the Regatta in 1999.
In the fall of 2009 he began writing a series of articles for the Pittsburgh Post-Gazette and Pollstar about his experiences in the music industry.
Topics so far have included The Beatles, The Del-Vikings, The Rolling Stones, Led Zeppelin, Bruce Springsteen, Janis Joplin, and the Pittsburgh Civic Arena.
In September 2014 his first book, entitled "Hard Days, Hard Nights" was released.
